                                "text": "tomas.kalibera@gmail.com"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n             Status|UNCONFIRMED                 |CLOSED\n         Resolution|---                         |Works as documented\n                 CC|                            |tomas.kalibera@gmail.com\n\n--- Comment #4 from Tomas Kalibera ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "mailto:tomas.kalibera@gmail.com",
                                "text": "tomas.kalibera@gmail.com"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") ---\nMulti-line variables in an Renviron file are not supported. The format is\nsimpler, just meant to set commonly needed variables. See the documentation in\n?Renviron:\n\n\"Lines in a site or user environment file should be either comment\nlines starting with ‘#’, or lines of the form ‘<name>=<value>’.\"\n\nPlease follow the documentation to see what is supported - not all features\nfrom a Unix shell are, and even some rules are slightly different. Yet, as the\ndocumentation says, it is recommended to use only the subset that works the\nsame way as in a Unix shell."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
